-- Orco Property, Polimex-Mostostal May Move: Central European Equity Preview
-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i   a n d   M o n i k a   R o z l a l
-- 2010-10-08T03:59:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-08/orco-property-polimex-mostostal-may-move-central-european-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in central European
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.
Share prices are from the last close.  Poland’s  WIG20 Index  fell 1.4 percent, the Czech  PX Index 
gained 0.2 percent and Hungary’s  BUX Index  rose 0.7 percent.  Orco Property Group SA  (ORCO CP): The governor of the
Warsaw province approved resumption of the developer’s flagship
Zlota 44 project, a residential tower designed by  Daniel Libeskind . Orco jumped 5.3 percent to 199 koruna.  Polimex-Mostostal SA  (PXM PW): Torpol, a unit of Poland’s
largest builder, won two construction orders with combined value
of 316 million zloty ($110.2 million) from Polish state
railways. Polimex shares declined 1.6 percent to 4.33 zloty.  To contact the reporters on this story:
